wikipedia_page.main: David Bailey "Beili" Davies (3 December 1884 – 24 August 1968) was a Welsh rugby union fullback who played club rugby for Oxford University, Llanelli and London Welsh and international rugby for Wales. In his personal life he was a schoolmaster, clergyman and soldier.
